25:24.948 --> 25:28.752
We turned in our report, were patted
on our heads, and told to hit the road.

25:28.852 --> 25:30.895
That's not exactly what happened.

25:30.995 --> 25:34.090
Oh, really? Then tell me what did.

25:35.124 --> 25:37.227
We wrapped up our job.

25:37.327 --> 25:38.661
Our job?

25:38.761 --> 25:42.499
The one we agreed to do
and get paid for. Our job.

25:42.599 --> 25:47.231
So, discovering, interpreting,
what could potentially change the world...

25:47.331 --> 25:49.706
...change the world, that's just a job?

25:49.806 --> 25:51.641
Change the world?

25:52.508 --> 25:55.111
- I know the world should be changed.
- It needs to be changed.

25:55.211 --> 25:58.014
But saying this discovery could is extreme.

25:58.114 --> 25:59.963
No, it isn't, Daniel.

26:00.063 --> 26:03.586
If what we've found out was made public,
then everyone's beliefs in reality...

26:03.686 --> 26:06.522
- ...in history, would transform.
- Maybe.

26:06.622 --> 26:08.901
No maybe. You know I'm right about this.

26:09.001 --> 26:10.761
- Fine, you're right.
- Thank you, professor.

26:10.861 --> 26:14.572
But are you sure you're not pissed just
because we might not be getting credit?

26:16.432 --> 26:18.268
Yeah, that's me, all right.

26:18.368 --> 26:21.538
My goal's always been to be
interviewed by fake news.

26:22.338 --> 26:24.206
I'm sorry.

26:25.007 --> 26:26.543
I know that's not you.

26:27.343 --> 26:28.978
Apology accepted.

26:36.552 --> 26:38.588
Okay, I'm listening.

26:39.688 --> 26:41.224
Tell us what you want us to do.

26:41.324 --> 26:44.794
Daniel, I just want us to somehow
follow this through.

26:44.894 --> 26:48.832
I just want to find out who really wrote
those inscriptions. Why did she risk so...

26:48.932 --> 26:51.267
- If it was a she.
- It was.

26:51.367 --> 26:57.374
Why did she risk so much for her Lord God
and her world of 14,000 years ago?

26:57.874 --> 27:00.943
A world that was much more advanced than now.

27:01.043 --> 27:03.479
- That's also kind of major, isn't it?
- Yes.

27:03.579 --> 27:04.833
And what happened to them?

27:04.933 --> 27:08.555
- Why, how, did their civilization vanish?
- That's a good question.

27:08.655 --> 27:12.016
And why aren't we being allowed
to search for the answers?

27:12.116 --> 27:13.356
I don't know.

27:13.456 --> 27:16.960
And no clue as to what Kontral's bosses
are planning on doing next.

27:17.060 --> 27:19.195
- True.
- I mean, who are those guys anyway?

27:19.295 --> 27:21.998
They certainly didn't make me
feel especially warm and fuzzy.

27:22.098 --> 27:23.532
Same.

27:25.267 --> 27:26.802
So?

27:30.639 --> 27:33.743
Fuck 'em, we go public.

27:33.843 --> 27:34.711
Yes.

27:34.811 --> 27:37.113
Right, we tell the world.
We give fake that interview.

27:37.413 --> 27:42.085
That is why you are still
the man and I love, you know.

27:42.185 --> 27:44.186
- I do.
- Yeah.

27:46.388 --> 27:49.425
- Ready for that drink?
- Yes, to celebrate.

27:49.525 --> 27:52.361
- Agreed.
- All right.

27:54.863 --> 27:56.932
Oh, crap.

27:57.035 --> 27:59.169
What's wrong with the... can you help me?

27:59.269 --> 28:00.870
- Okay.
- No, Scout.

28:00.970 --> 28:02.834
Oh, sure.

28:09.378 --> 28:12.188
- You know you drive me nuts.
- That's my job.

28:16.885 --> 28:18.687
Crazy kids.

28:23.393 --> 28:25.461
Hey, it's interview time.

28:34.930 --> 28:36.926
Hello, handsome.

28:48.250 --> 28:50.520
My God, what happened?

28:50.620 --> 28:54.890
Dr. Allen, Miss Turner.
Are you all right? Are you okay?

29:11.506 --> 29:13.719
Guess we'll do this the fun way.

29:57.386 --> 30:01.317
- Ready to proceed?
- Definitely, showtime.

30:01.723 --> 30:02.724
Resolution?

30:02.824 --> 30:06.493
It's not gonna moisten Halo's pants,
but it's kickin'.

30:06.863 --> 30:08.631
I'll take that as a good.

30:08.731 --> 30:13.002
548 ultra, ultra sensitive
suckers kissing it.

30:13.102 --> 30:17.406
Feeding into this hungry maxi gig baby.

30:17.506 --> 30:19.275
Yeah, it's killer good.

30:19.375 --> 30:22.377
- Just get on with the tour, please.
- Going in.

30:22.945 --> 30:27.981
Now, the images are pretty accurate
but what we're seeing is anybody's guess.

30:30.051 --> 30:33.289
Something bad coming up. Bonus points.

30:33.389 --> 30:37.126
- Zoom in and enhance.
- Aye, captain.

30:37.459 --> 30:38.928
We're going in.

30:41.030 --> 30:42.482
Holy crap.

30:42.582 --> 30:44.801
Get more detail on that.

30:45.401 --> 30:46.969
We're at max.

30:47.069 --> 30:50.073
Another piece to the puzzle.

30:50.173 --> 30:52.421
A Rubik's cube.

30:53.408 --> 30:55.645
An appropriate analogy.

31:26.175 --> 31:27.544
- Mr. Kontral.
- What is it?

31:27.644 --> 31:29.935
I'd like to show you something, sir.

31:36.219 --> 31:39.389
Zero effect. Like a diamond.

31:39.489 --> 31:42.892
- Denser. Infinitely.
- Now that's interesting.

31:42.992 --> 31:47.096
It would take something nuclear tipped
to break this baby apart.

31:47.196 --> 31:49.899
Well, that's never out of the question.

31:49.999 --> 31:52.602
- You can do that?
- You have no idea what I can do.

31:52.702 --> 31:54.555
- Shit.
- But then we'd lose...

31:54.655 --> 31:57.640
...our little discovery wouldn't we,
if I went all Strangelove on it?

31:57.740 --> 32:02.212
And I do so want to know
what secrets you contain.

32:02.312 --> 32:04.581
Kontral, you are one supreme prick.

32:04.681 --> 32:07.050
That's an understatement, Scout.

32:07.150 --> 32:09.569
- And he's sitting on...
- The discovery of the century.

32:09.669 --> 32:11.988
Another understatement.

32:12.088 --> 32:16.789
Then I suggest, sir, that you decide
what you want to do ASAP.

32:17.592 --> 32:19.762
You do? And why is that?

32:19.862 --> 32:24.667
Our sensors are indicating increased,
growing activity inside.

32:24.767 --> 32:27.603
Circuits, engines, something is starting up.

32:27.703 --> 32:29.639
- It's reactivating?
- Yes.

32:29.739 --> 32:31.074
That's interesting.

32:31.174 --> 32:33.644
And I think it's getting ready to take off.

32:34.444 --> 32:37.680
Now, after waiting 14,000 years?

32:37.780 --> 32:41.150
My guess is that it was covered
under tons of ore that buried it.

32:41.250 --> 32:45.988
And when we scraped it off, something
inside said it could now break free.

32:46.088 --> 32:47.690
Well, can it?

32:47.790 --> 32:50.966
I have no idea of knowing its power but...

32:51.066 --> 32:53.463
...I'm pretty damn sure
that's what it's preparing to do.

32:53.563 --> 32:56.466
Well, we're just going to have
to change its plans, aren't we?

32:56.566 --> 32:58.468
You're the boss.

32:58.568 --> 33:00.435
Yes, I am.

33:10.245 --> 33:13.516
- <i>Doctor Allen, I presume.</i>
- Crap.

33:13.816 --> 33:15.684
Stay down.

33:17.386 --> 33:19.555
It's time for the world to know, Kontral.

33:19.655 --> 33:24.863
Now why on Earth would you come
to that conclusion? Nicole.

33:25.510 --> 33:27.213
Lock on and execute.

33:37.372 --> 33:38.528
No!

33:40.742 --> 33:42.611
I'm sorry.

33:42.878 --> 33:45.681
I couldn't finish our job.

33:48.184 --> 33:50.397
Oh, no!

33:58.093 --> 34:00.561
Hey, hey.

34:01.296 --> 34:04.756
It's okay. It's okay. It's just a dream.

34:05.734 --> 34:09.338
- Death and destruction.
- That's a worry.

34:09.438 --> 34:12.141
Everything was burning
and I couldn't stop it.

34:12.241 --> 34:15.411
It's okay. It was just a dream.

34:15.511 --> 34:17.045
Remember?

34:17.512 --> 34:21.317
- Yeah, sorry, sorry.
- Don't be sorry.

34:22.284 --> 34:26.321
- It was really scary.
- Yeah, I figured that.

34:29.491 --> 34:31.360
You're so smart.

34:34.228 --> 34:36.031
And lovable.

34:36.130 --> 34:37.933
Just barely.

34:38.833 --> 34:40.803
Can you hold me?

34:40.902 --> 34:42.771
If I must.

34:48.110 --> 34:49.744
Feel good?

34:49.844 --> 34:51.679
It does.

34:52.013 --> 34:54.016
Mission accomplished.

34:55.784 --> 34:59.555
<i>Remember, we are God's creation.</i>

34:59.655 --> 35:04.433
<i>And the creator of all has placed
his divine instructions in the scriptures...</i>

35:04.533 --> 35:07.497
<i>...telling us, no, instructing us...</i>

35:07.597 --> 35:10.890
<i>...that it is our right, our destiny...</i>

35:10.990 --> 35:16.639
<i>...to enrich ourselves from the world's
limitless ever plentiful resources.</i>

35:17.139 --> 35:18.973
<i>We must...</i>

35:19.508 --> 35:23.579
This is where you should be.
Good food and good people.

35:24.512 --> 35:27.283
- Thank you.
- You're quite welcome.

35:27.383 --> 35:30.818
Now promise me you'll find
your way home. Okay?

35:30.918 --> 35:32.754
God bless you.

35:33.922 --> 35:35.757
You too.

35:36.425 --> 35:40.996
<i>Sharon Turner, 22, is being sought
for the brutal murder of Daniel Allen.</i>

35:41.096 --> 35:44.404
<i>Allen's charred and dismembered body
was discovered late last night...</i>

35:44.504 --> 35:47.536
<i>...by firefighters in his Oak Palm apartment.</i>

35:47.636 --> 35:51.083
<i>Allen and Turner were reported to
have been romantically involved...</i>

35:51.183 --> 35:54.811
<i>...and that Allen had repeatedly
tried to end their affair.</i>

36:09.391 --> 36:12.629
You can't occupy a booth
without ordering something.

36:13.779 --> 36:14.894
Coffee.

36:20.201 --> 36:22.005
I didn't order that.

36:22.505 --> 36:25.674
No coffee for you. No coffee period.

36:25.774 --> 36:30.246
Fucking spill by the fucking upstream
chem plant contaminated the town's water.

36:30.346 --> 36:32.648
My idiot boss should close the place.

36:32.748 --> 36:34.543
Bad news.

36:34.643 --> 36:38.654
Yeah. Anyway, you need this more than coffee.

36:38.754 --> 36:41.791
It's no charge. You look like crap.

36:41.891 --> 36:44.976
Thanks, for the sundae.

36:45.076 --> 36:47.930
No big deal. Nobody orders dessert anymore.

36:48.030 --> 36:51.533
- It's like a world gone mad.
- Yeah.

36:51.633 --> 36:53.635
Do you need a job?

36:54.169 --> 36:56.604
No, I'm okay.

36:56.771 --> 36:58.307
Yeah, right.

36:58.407 --> 37:01.911
Look, if they ever clean up this water mess,
they're gonna need help here.

37:02.011 --> 37:05.815
It's not too shitty once the owner gets
the message you're not going to blow him.

37:05.915 --> 37:07.716
No, really.

37:08.116 --> 37:09.651
Okay.

37:13.288 --> 37:14.823
Snot.

37:16.548 --> 37:18.076
Yeah.

37:21.462 --> 37:23.066
Tears.

37:24.016 --> 37:25.817
Can't stop 'em.

37:27.302 --> 37:29.170
Bad news?

37:29.604 --> 37:31.673
Bad, bad day.

37:31.773 --> 37:34.444
Mary, when we gonna get some coffee?

37:34.774 --> 37:36.645
Ask the president.

37:38.546 --> 37:40.381
How bad?

37:41.282 --> 37:43.151
Real bad.

37:43.251 --> 37:44.786
Lost...

37:45.220 --> 37:47.756
- Your guy?
- Yeah.

37:49.257 --> 37:50.789
No...

37:52.741 --> 37:54.802
...he wasn't just a guy.

37:56.064 --> 37:58.535
He was the only one who saw the real me.

37:59.435 --> 38:01.671
He was my best friend before he was...

38:02.171 --> 38:05.875
Look, life goes on, hon. You'll find another.

38:05.975 --> 38:07.828
He was killed today.

38:08.676 --> 38:11.513
- Fuck.
- Murdered.

38:12.313 --> 38:14.191
Double fuck.

38:14.934 --> 38:17.453
- And they're going to get away with it.
- What are you saying?

38:17.553 --> 38:19.355
They're too rich, they're too powerful.

38:19.455 --> 38:22.739
I don't know what happened.
I don't want to know. But...

38:22.839 --> 38:25.079
- ...you got to make them pay somehow.
- But I can't.

38:25.179 --> 38:29.266
Somehow. You can't let
the bad guys always win.

38:30.366 --> 38:32.802
And you must fulfill your destiny.

38:34.804 --> 38:37.177
Always ringing at the wrong time.

38:38.407 --> 38:41.878
And I hate that it's always
broadcasting your location.

38:42.378 --> 38:44.245
Stay brave.

39:39.467 --> 39:41.203
Good evening.

39:41.303 --> 39:43.629
Good evening again...

39:43.729 --> 39:45.874
...one and all.

39:45.974 --> 39:49.932
You know why we requested
your presence, don't you, Richard?

39:50.032 --> 39:53.682
- I can guess.
- Don't guess. Tell us.

39:53.982 --> 39:55.484
Please.

39:55.950 --> 39:59.889
To explain why the ancient craft
has yet to be disposed of.

39:59.989 --> 40:01.390
Destroyed.

40:01.490 --> 40:05.094
The harlot captured. And eliminated.

40:05.194 --> 40:08.197
You know that I will ultimately
follow your orders.

40:08.297 --> 40:09.966
Ultimately?

40:11.982 --> 40:15.603
I... please do not misinterpret.

40:15.703 --> 40:19.323
- Are we?
- I pray not...

40:19.423 --> 40:22.209
...but I would, once again...

40:22.309 --> 40:25.249
...wish to request more time...

40:25.349 --> 40:27.749
...to access its inner workings.

40:27.849 --> 40:30.937
We grow weary of explaining to you
that whatever it contains...

40:31.037 --> 40:35.157
...can not counter the negative
cultural effects of its existence.

40:35.257 --> 40:38.694
Even, even if it were not constructed...

40:38.794 --> 40:41.630
...by creatures, monsters,
from some other world...

40:41.730 --> 40:44.500
...but built instead by humans...

40:44.600 --> 40:49.837
...identical to us from some long past age?

40:50.038 --> 40:51.974
Even more so.

40:52.074 --> 40:55.711
Certainly, you have not forgotten
that such knowledge of their existence...

40:55.811 --> 40:58.651
...would undermine
our prime means of control.

41:01.749 --> 41:05.454
- Of course not.
- The time for closure has now arrived.

41:05.554 --> 41:08.778
- Has passed.
- And...

41:08.878 --> 41:13.428
...I will immediately fulfill your wishes.

41:13.528 --> 41:17.400
The relic ground into dust
and scattered to the wind.

41:17.600 --> 41:19.335
The harlot?

41:19.435 --> 41:21.871
Located and butchered, of course.

41:22.571 --> 41:24.707
See that you do.

41:24.807 --> 41:26.308
I will.

41:26.408 --> 41:28.242
Good evening, Richard.

41:35.216 --> 41:36.751
Fuck.

41:38.721 --> 41:41.357
<i>What's up? Oh, yes, sir, Mr. Kontral.</i>

41:41.457 --> 41:43.959
I'm accelerating the examination
of our project.

41:44.059 --> 41:47.529
- <i>Cool.</i>
- Be prepared to begin with...

41:48.864 --> 41:50.966
This the harlot you're looking for, shithead?

41:51.066 --> 41:53.335
So melodramatic.

41:53.435 --> 41:55.604
How on Earth did you manage to get in here?

41:55.704 --> 41:58.640
Amazing what some guys'll do
for major blow job.

41:58.740 --> 42:02.511
- From you? I don't think so.
- I care not.

42:02.611 --> 42:05.815
You do realize you're not getting
out of here alive, don't you, dear?

42:05.915 --> 42:08.517
- Kind of figured that.
- So why the visit?

42:08.617 --> 42:11.453
- To slit your fucking throat.
- Oh, such malice.

42:11.553 --> 42:15.057
- Yes, that's me.
- How blandly lower middle class.

42:15.157 --> 42:18.467
Just because we butchered
your pathetic little sweetheart?

42:21.312 --> 42:24.166
- Fuck.
- On your knees.

42:24.634 --> 42:27.068
Listen to her.

42:30.990 --> 42:34.410
It's the only way you're ever gonna
get a woman to do that, you creep.

42:34.510 --> 42:39.381
Why must you continuously insist on
referencing such an unpleasant subject?

42:39.481 --> 42:43.052
- Fuck you.
- I do like your attitude.

42:43.152 --> 42:48.007
So come on, tell me.
Just to satisfy my ever inquiring mind...

42:48.107 --> 42:50.650
...how did you manage to slip by security?

42:51.961 --> 42:55.197
No sweat. Your girlfriend
stepped out for a smoke.

42:55.297 --> 42:57.299
Nicole, I'm disappointed.

42:57.399 --> 43:00.569
Your bosses need
a higher level of employment.

43:00.669 --> 43:03.872
Oh, well, it's a national problem.

43:04.339 --> 43:08.978
I am sorry we didn't get to spend
more quality time together, Sharon.

43:09.578 --> 43:12.347
Oh, well. Dispose of her.

43:12.447 --> 43:15.377
That you'll find she's really very good at.

43:15.617 --> 43:17.553
<i>Holy shit.</i>

43:19.353 --> 43:21.588
That's awkward.

43:22.356 --> 43:25.494
You... heard our whole little confrontation?

43:26.396 --> 43:28.197
<i>I know nothing.</i>

43:28.697 --> 43:30.999
Help me. Don't let this...

43:32.267 --> 43:35.304
Now my hand is seriously pained.

43:36.537 --> 43:39.908
It's about time we put an end
to your sad little story.

43:40.008 --> 43:42.111
- <i>Mr. Kontral?</i>
- What?

43:42.211 --> 43:45.581
<i>When that woman comes on camera,
the readings here, they blast off the charts.</i>

43:45.681 --> 43:48.801
- What do you mean?
- <i>From the spaceship.</i>

43:48.901 --> 43:51.703
- Really?
- <i>Yep.</i>

43:52.186 --> 43:54.190
What, when it saw her?

43:54.990 --> 43:56.992
Point your camera at her.

44:03.446 --> 44:05.168
Change of plan.

44:05.800 --> 44:10.391
Bring her along with us.
Secure her in the usual manner.

44:16.711 --> 44:19.208
Welcome, Sharon.

44:22.183 --> 44:25.988
Now let's see if you really are
essential to this historic puzzle.

44:26.088 --> 44:27.886
Fuck you.

44:27.986 --> 44:29.876
Check the readouts.

44:30.726 --> 44:32.227
Shazam.

44:32.327 --> 44:34.191
All right, here, let me have that.

44:36.565 --> 44:39.280
Well, now that is very interesting.

44:39.380 --> 44:43.005
You really are linked
to our little project, aren't you?

44:43.105 --> 44:47.209
All I did was interpret some etchings.
Just doing my job, you creep.

44:47.309 --> 44:50.412
No, you're far more than that,
way beyond random coincidence.

44:50.512 --> 44:54.917
This ship lying dormant for thousands of
years and then reacting now only to you.

44:55.017 --> 44:56.825
Serendipity?

44:56.925 --> 44:58.687
Oh, I don't think so.

44:58.787 --> 45:01.132
Chess pieces are being moved.

45:01.232 --> 45:03.157
Go fuck yourself.

45:03.295 --> 45:04.596
Now, Sharon...

45:04.696 --> 45:08.155
...if you're going to be part of history,
you'll have to be a little more elegant.

45:10.831 --> 45:13.135
It just can't wait to meet you.

45:13.235 --> 45:14.570
Easy with the camera.

45:14.670 --> 45:17.107
Bill me. Come on, let's take a little walk.

45:19.307 --> 45:21.157
I'll stay here and man the shop.

45:27.381 --> 45:29.184
Stay close.

45:30.418 --> 45:34.319
And those idiots wanted me
to destroy this treasure.

45:35.656 --> 45:37.162
Bring her.

45:42.913 --> 45:45.351
Well, you were right about one thing.

45:45.601 --> 45:48.203
- It is beautiful.
- It's not yours.

45:48.303 --> 45:49.538
Oh, whose is it?

45:49.638 --> 45:51.473
- It belongs to...
- To the world?

45:51.573 --> 45:54.175
- To science?
- Yes.

45:55.376 --> 45:58.178
Well, that's not going to happen.
Give me your gun.

45:58.278 --> 46:01.717
So you and I are going to continue
our little walk alone.

46:01.817 --> 46:04.853
Just to see what happens. Move.

46:07.688 --> 46:11.530
Don't be frightened. I have a very strong
feeling this thing doesn't want to harm you.

46:11.630 --> 46:13.595
Yeah, well, hopefully
that doesn't include you.

46:13.695 --> 46:15.229
Wait.

46:17.331 --> 46:20.698
A valid concern. On your knees.

46:20.798 --> 46:22.061
- What?
- On your knees.

46:22.161 --> 46:25.573
- You're fucking kidding me.
- I never kid. Just do it.

46:25.993 --> 46:28.409
Put your hands on the surface. Touch it.

46:32.664 --> 46:35.133
It is so exited to see you.

46:36.083 --> 46:37.953
Now, what do you feel?

46:38.553 --> 46:40.789
I said, what do you feel?

46:43.491 --> 46:46.727
It's cold, powerful.

46:47.595 --> 46:51.032
Wonderful. Cold power.

46:51.492 --> 46:55.151
Wonderful. Thank you, Sharon.

46:55.251 --> 46:58.222
I don't think I could have
put it any better myself.

46:58.322 --> 47:00.946
See, that's what this has all been about.

47:01.046 --> 47:03.311
Cold power, Sharon.

47:03.686 --> 47:06.190
Cold power and when I have it
at my command...

47:06.290 --> 47:10.091
...when I control it, I mean fully
control it, and in my control alone...

47:10.191 --> 47:15.330
...then I'll take that power and the world
will have to listen to Richard Kontral!

47:18.976 --> 47:20.311
Asshole.

47:48.423 --> 47:49.778
Oh, shit.

48:04.338 --> 48:06.593
Time for a smoke.

48:06.693 --> 48:08.373
Nice tin man.

48:08.909 --> 48:10.911
Nice tin man.

48:14.081 --> 48:16.151
Have fun tonight, bitch.

48:47.715 --> 48:49.250
Hello?

48:53.203 --> 48:54.789
Hello?

48:55.256 --> 48:58.900
Anybody out there? How's it going?

49:02.997 --> 49:04.532
Hello?

50:37.391 --> 50:40.619
You don't want to miss
the whole adventure, do you?

51:12.526 --> 51:15.897
Your awakening has been
duly noted by our tall friend.

51:15.997 --> 51:17.732
Oh, God.

51:17.832 --> 51:21.502
- And he appears to be very interested...
- Shut the fuck up.

51:32.430 --> 51:34.365
Take your clothes off.

51:35.000 --> 51:38.903
- What, and get on my knees?
- Oh, please, you're not that irresistible.

51:41.589 --> 51:43.391
Take them off.

51:44.241 --> 51:47.696
- Do it, or it's going to.
- Okay, okay, okay.

52:15.006 --> 52:17.626
- What?
- Socks, don't forget your socks.

52:17.726 --> 52:19.594
Stop helping me.

52:57.930 --> 53:00.267
Queen of outer space.

53:01.869 --> 53:04.320
You have no idea of how close you are.

53:07.475 --> 53:11.379
Well, then, would you please enlighten me.

53:11.479 --> 53:13.682
Since when did we become friends?

53:14.182 --> 53:16.986
Slitting your throat
is still my number one priority.

53:17.686 --> 53:19.788
Well, that's a real shame.

53:19.888 --> 53:22.925
And here I thought
we were getting along so well.

53:43.243 --> 53:44.779
Forward.

53:49.950 --> 53:52.688
- Even Mr. Ray Charles, right?
- What?

53:54.088 --> 53:56.463
Nothing of interest.

54:15.325 --> 54:18.346
The moon? We're there?

54:18.946 --> 54:22.484
- Apparently so.
- So fast. How is that possible?

54:22.584 --> 54:25.293
Super science. Super power.

54:25.819 --> 54:29.057
- So, you haven't a clue.
- Not a one.

55:31.585 --> 55:35.393
You're the first woman on the moon,
I believe. Any appropriate words?

55:35.493 --> 55:37.323
Fuck off.

55:37.792 --> 55:39.561
And you're wrong.

55:39.661 --> 55:41.495
How so?

55:44.664 --> 55:46.533
I've met her twin sister.

55:48.317 --> 55:49.875
Who is she?

56:11.224 --> 56:15.769
Curiouser and curiouser grows our tale.

57:23.130 --> 57:26.434
- Well, that was entertaining.
- Since when did you become comedy relief?

57:26.534 --> 57:29.203
- Oh, please, by no means.
- Just shut the hell up.

57:29.303 --> 57:32.173
Don't say another word to me. Got it?

57:32.273 --> 57:34.107
Got it.

58:17.034 --> 58:18.984
Oh, you got to be kidding me.

58:20.754 --> 58:24.592
Sure, after flying to the moon
and getting attacked by a killer robot...

58:24.692 --> 58:27.995
...how difficult can it be
to put on an ancient space suit?

58:28.095 --> 58:29.929
Why not?

58:35.269 --> 58:36.904
Okay.

58:37.537 --> 58:39.440
Ready for whatever.

58:39.540 --> 58:43.080
I have to say I'm very curious
to see what awaits you.

58:45.446 --> 58:48.048
Stop, stop, stop!

58:48.412 --> 58:50.618
Thank you. Thank you.

58:52.387 --> 58:54.289
Thank you so much.

58:54.389 --> 58:56.898
Thank you. Thank you.

59:02.679 --> 59:05.592
But why, why did you do that?

59:07.200 --> 59:08.936
Not sure.

59:09.036 --> 59:11.132
Maybe I'm just a good person.

59:12.472 --> 59:14.341
Thank you.

59:14.775 --> 59:18.446
- I really thought I was...
- Or maybe I wanted to kill you myself.

59:22.716 --> 59:24.384
Whatever.

59:24.985 --> 59:26.971
Just be careful.

59:27.071 --> 59:29.541
We're in this together now, you know.

59:31.695 --> 59:33.992
Come back in one piece, okay?

59:47.007 --> 59:50.042
No, fuck you.

01:00:33.787 --> 01:00:35.589
Journey's end.

01:02:07.647 --> 01:02:12.119
Watching, learning while you were dreaming...

01:02:12.619 --> 01:02:15.455
...my sweet little scout.

01:02:37.563 --> 01:02:39.113
Easy, easy.

01:02:46.753 --> 01:02:50.823
Up, up, up, and away we go.

01:02:57.097 --> 01:03:01.349
Homeward bound, nice and steady,
nice and steady.

01:03:01.836 --> 01:03:04.269
Second star on the right...

01:03:04.805 --> 01:03:07.221
...and straight on to morning.

01:03:14.648 --> 01:03:16.450
Damn you.

01:03:44.794 --> 01:03:46.616
Now what?

01:04:03.630 --> 01:04:05.165
Asshole.

01:06:32.478 --> 01:06:34.313
I'll try.

01:06:34.414 --> 01:06:36.249
I'll try.

01:09:14.273 --> 01:09:16.076
Dear God...

01:09:16.734 --> 01:09:18.551
...what have I done?

01:13:55.388 --> 01:13:57.635
I'm going to follow it through, Daniel.

01:13:58.625 --> 01:14:00.427
Finish our job.

01:14:31.290 --> 01:14:32.825
Garen.

01:14:35.962 --> 01:14:37.764
Waiting for Mya.

01:14:46.739 --> 01:14:50.878
<i>Long ago, the Krell crystal
created a world for our people.</i>

01:14:50.978 --> 01:14:54.581
<i>The crystal's origin was unknown,
lost in time.</i>

01:14:54.681 --> 01:14:57.451
<i>When destruction
from the stars was foretold...</i>

01:14:57.551 --> 01:15:00.887
<i>...Lord God Garen bid me
to bring the Krell to this world...</i>

01:15:00.987 --> 01:15:03.957
<i>...so he could prepare
a new home for our people.</i>

01:15:04.057 --> 01:15:09.028
<i>But I failed, so I have selected you
to fulfill my destiny.</i>

01:15:18.804 --> 01:15:21.321
Will you one day be awakened...

01:15:21.421 --> 01:15:24.272
...and thanked for making this new world...

01:15:26.217 --> 01:15:28.441
...my Lord God Garen?

01:15:32.985 --> 01:15:35.065
On your knees, Sharon.

01:16:02.014 --> 01:16:03.415
Hey.

01:16:04.917 --> 01:16:06.352
Hey.

01:16:06.719 --> 01:16:08.154
Here.

01:16:09.491 --> 01:16:11.357
Right here.

01:16:11.457 --> 01:16:13.926
Come on. Come on.

01:16:20.299 --> 01:16:23.339
Hey, I'll get on my knees.

01:17:35.257 --> 01:17:37.099
Queen of outer space?

01:17:38.477 --> 01:17:40.312
No way.

01:18:02.268 --> 01:18:04.469
Into the river of time.

